## Permission helpers

Quick presets for common configurations:

```ts
import {
  createNodeDriver,
  allowAll,
  allowAllFs,
  allowAllNetwork,
} from "secure-exec";

// Allow everything
const driver = createNodeDriver({ permissions: allowAll });

// Allow only filesystem and network
const selective = createNodeDriver({
  permissions: {
    fs: allowAllFs,
    network: allowAllNetwork,
  },
});
```

| Export | Allows |
|---|---|
| `allowAll` | All operations across all domains |
| `allowAllFs` | All filesystem reads and writes |
| `allowAllNetwork` | All network requests and DNS lookups |
| `allowAllChildProcess` | All child process spawning |
| `allowAllEnv` | All environment variable access |

## Function-based checks

Each permission field accepts a function that inspects the request and returns a decision:

```ts
const driver = createNodeDriver({
  permissions: {
    fs: (req) => ({ allow: req.operation === "read" }),
    network: (req) => ({ allow: !req.host?.endsWith(".internal") }),
    childProcess: (req) => ({ allow: ["node", "python3"].includes(req.command) }),
    env: (req) => ({ allow: ["PATH", "HOME"].includes(req.name) }),
  },
});
```

## Permissions type

```ts
type PermissionDecision =
  | boolean
  | { allowed: boolean; reason?: string }
  | { allow: boolean; reason?: string };

type PermissionCheck<T> = (request: T) => PermissionDecision;

type Permissions = {
  fs?: PermissionCheck<{ path: string; operation: string }>;
  network?: PermissionCheck<{ url?: string; host?: string; port?: number }>;
  childProcess?: PermissionCheck<{ command: string; args: string[] }>;
  env?: PermissionCheck<{ name: string; value: string }>;
};
```

